         MACRO
         COMMEXIT
COMMEXIT DSECT
***********************************************************************
*
*        MAP OF THE COMMON EXIT PARAMETER AREA PASSED TO ALL
*        SMF EXITS.  THE FIELDS AND BIT SETTING DOCUMENTATION ARE FOR
*        VS/2 (MVS).
*
*        INSTALLED ON: 04/25/78; BY: DGH.
*
*        MODIFIED ON 08/17/79; BY: DGH TO ADD SELECTIVE 322/722 ABEND
*              SUPPORT
*
*        MODIFIED ON 12/09/79; BY: DGH TO ADD DSN CONTENTION
*              RE-QUEUE FACILITY
*
*        11/23/81(DGH) - INSTALL BYPASS CODE; FEATURE PERMITS ALL
*          SMF EXITS TO BE BYPASSED IF BYPASS FLAG IS SET.
*          BYPASS FLAG IS SET BY SMF EXIT IEFUJV (SEE SMF EXIT
*          IEFUJV FOR FURTHER DETAILS).
*
***********************************************************************
CEPJOBN  DS    CL8           JOBNAME
CEPRDRTM DS    BL4           TIME, IN HUNDREDTHS OF SECONDS, THAT RDR
*                            RECOGNIZED JOB CARD.
CEPRDRDT DS    PL4           JOB READER DATE; FORMAT 00YYDDDF
CEPSYSID DS    CL4           4-BYTE SID PARM FROM SMFPRMXX
CEPUSRID DS    CL8           8-BYTE USER ID FIELD
         ORG       CEPUSRID       RE-MAP THE USER ID FIELD
CEPIDFLG DS        XL1            FLAGS USED BY SMF
CEPIDF01 EQU       X'01'          'TEST JOB '
CEPIDF02 EQU       X'02'          BATCH JOB
CEPIDF03 EQU       X'04'          TSO SESSION
CEPIDF04 EQU       X'08'          SYSTEM TASK
CEPIDF05 EQU       X'10'          BYPASS FLAG - DO NOT USE EXIT IF ON
CEPIDF06 EQU       X'20'          DIAGNOSTIC FLAG - DUMP/DISPLAY
CEPIDF07 EQU       X'40'          'REGION=' ON JOB STMT IS A DEFAULT
CEPIDCLS DS        CL1            INITIATED JOB CLASS (SET BY IEFUJI)
CEPIDJES DS        BL2            JES JOB #, IN BINARY
CEPIDPTY DS        XL1            JES JOB SELECTION PRIORITY(REVISED)
CEPIDSCL DS        CL1            SCHEDULED JOB CLASS (SET BY IEFUJV)
         DS        CL2            (RESERVED)
CEPSTEP# DS    BL1           # OF THE STEP CURRENTLY BEING PROCESSED
CEPSMFOP DS    BL1           SMF OPTION INDICATORS (MEANING WHEN SET)
CEPSMF00 EQU   X'80'         SYSTEM AND JOB ACCOUNTING (OPT=1)
CEPSMF01 EQU   X'40'         SYSTEM, JOB, AND STEP ACCOUNTING (OPT=2)
CEPSMF02 EQU   X'20'         USER EXITS WILL BE TAKEN (EXT=YES)
CEPSMF03 EQU   X'10'         DATA SET ACCOUNTING (DSV=2 OR 3)
CEPSMF04 EQU   X'08'         VOLUME ACCOUNTING (DSV=1 OR 3)
CEPSMF05 EQU   X'04'         RESERVED
CEPSMF06 EQU   X'02'         TYPE 17 RECS WILL BE WRITTEN FOR TEMP D.S.
CEPSMF07 EQU   X'01'         0=BACKGROUND JOB;1=FOREGROUND JOB
CEPRSTOP DS    BL1           RESTART OPTIONS (MEANING WHEN SET)
CEPRST00 EQU   X'80'         STEP RESTART
CEPRST01 EQU   X'40'         CHECKPOINT/RESTART
CEPRST02 EQU   X'20'         CONTINUE RESTART
CEPRST03 EQU   X'10'         RESERVED
CEPRST04 EQU   X'08'         WARM START
CEPRST05 EQU   X'04'         RESERVED
CEPRST06 EQU   X'02'         RESERVED
CEPRST07 EQU   X'01'         RESERVED
CEPCLASS DS    CL1           JOB CLASS
CEPUSER  DS    F             USER COMMUNICATION FIELD
CEPLGTH  EQU   *-COMMEXIT    LENGTH OF THIS AREA
         MEND
